UNWORTHINESS TO INHERIT
The following shall be unworthy of inheriting either on the basis of an Act or on the basis of a will and shall not obtain anything on the basis of a will:
a person who has intentionally taken the life of the decedent or attempted to do so;
a person who by duress or threat forced the decedent or tricked him or her into making or revoking a will or a provision in a will, or who prevented the decedent from doing so;
a person who has destroyed or hidden the decedent's will with the intention of preventing the fulfilment of the decedent's will, as well as a person who has forged the decedent's will;
a person who failed in his or her duty to maintain the decedent despite being bound by an Act to do so, as well as a person who refused to provide the decedent help he or she needed.
